UNITED STATES of America v. Howard HENRY. No. 3597. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. May 10, 1949. Lester Luther, U. S. Atty., and Eugene W. Davis, and Philip A. Dergance, Asst. U. S. Attys., Topeka, Kan., for appellant. Rooney, Dickinson & Prager, Topeka, Kan., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, Chief Judge, and BRATTON and. MURRAH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed May 10, 1949, pursuant to stipulation.
